      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-r&#34; data-lang=&#34;r&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(haven) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#read_sav()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(mediation) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# mediate() (Tingley, Yamamoto, Hirose, Keele, &amp;amp; Imai, 2014)&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(gvlma) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# gvlma()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(kableExtra) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#kable()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(corrr) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#correlate()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(psych) &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#mediate()&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;(tidyverse)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;mediation-in-r&#34;&gt;Mediation in R&#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;#mediation-in-r&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This examples comes from a tutorial paper on mediation found &#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.tqmp.org/RegularArticles/vol13-3/p148/p148.pdf&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&#xA;This is an open source paper that shared the data set used in this example.&#xA;The following is code and interpretation are based on this paper.&#xA;Note that they use a different package to estimate the model and you will see that our estimates are very close, though not exact.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
